欢迎来到亚特兰大  安德伍德夫人
Welcome to Atlanta, Mrs. Underwood.

35
00:03:19,620 --> 00:03:20,390
谢谢
Thank you.

36
00:03:20,390 --> 00:03:22,520
您能对希尔参议员的投票发表评论吗
Can you comment on Senator Sheer's vote?

37
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:25,530
我很荣幸  但我相信他是开玩笑的
Well, I am flattered. But it's all in good fun, I'm sure.

38
00:03:25,530 --> 00:03:27,740
安德伍德夫人  他说他还会再为您投票
Mrs. Underwood, he says he'll vote for you again.

39
00:03:27,740 --> 00:03:31,070
我鼓励所有人  包括参议员希尔
Well, I am encouraging everyone, including Senator Sheer,

40
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,520
把票投给凯茜·杜兰特
to vote for Cathy Durant.

41
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:33,510
总统和我
Both the president and I

42
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:36,120
都认为她是这个职位的最佳人选
think she is the best choice in the field.

43
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,900
你把我们写的稿全改了
You changed everything we wrote.

44
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:40,760
那个稿子没有创意  也不押韵
There was no imagination to it. No rhythm.

45
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:42,890
从他们就职就是我们在为他们写讲稿
We've been writing their speeches since they took office.

46
00:03:42,890 --> 00:03:44,350
我们知道自己在做什么
We know what we're doing.

47
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:47,780
你们在意的是好讲稿  还是撰稿人署名
Well, do you want it to be good, or do you want it to be yours?

48
00:03:48,290 --> 00:03:50,040
最让我激动的投票
The vote I'm most excited about

49
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,190
是昨天在众议院
is the victory our 

50
00:03:51,190 --> 00:03:54,130
我们的《背景普查法案》取得的胜利
Background Check Legislation got in the House yesterday.

51
00:03:54,130 --> 00:03:56,760
所以我希望参议院也能尽快向他们学习
So I'm hoping that the Senate will follow their lead soon,

52
00:03:56,770 --> 00:03:59,320
这样总统就能签署这一法案
and that the president can sign it into law.

53
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:01,560
我得走了  非常感谢
I have to go. Thank you so much.

54
00:04:02,860 --> 00:04:05,510
谢谢您邀请我们
Thank you... for inviting us.

55
00:04:05,660 --> 00:04:06,560
不
No.

56
00:04:07,270 --> 00:04:10,570
是我应该谢谢你和你儿子
It's me who has to thank you and your son.

57
00:04:10,570 --> 00:04:12,090
他救了我的命
He saved my life.

58
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,950
虽然是因为那样一场悲剧
No matter how tragic the circumstances.

59
00:04:16,830 --> 00:04:19,860
我想带你见见其他接受者
I want you to meet some of the other recipients.

60
00:04:20,230 --> 00:04:24,350
这是詹姆斯...接受了你儿子的一个肾
This is James... who received one of your son's kidneys.

61
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:28,350
这是路易莎
And this is Luisa...

62
00:04:28,860 --> 00:04:31,120
她接受了你儿子的心脏
who received your son's heart.

63
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:40,280
路易莎是名单中的第一个
Luisa was at the top of the list.

64
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,420
她再过几小时本就会死了
She was hours away from dying.

65
00:04:43,590 --> 00:04:45,980
如果可以的话  我们一起拍个照吧
Uh, if we could, let's all get together for a photo.

66
00:04:45,980 --> 00:04:47,430
詹姆斯  过来
James? Right here.

67
00:04:48,420 --> 00:04:50,700
-你到这儿来  -好的
- You come right here. - Okay.

68
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:52,760
这边  很好
This way. Great.

69
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:58,250
总统对他的移植手术并不避讳
The president isn't shying away from, uh, his transplant.

70
00:04:58,250 --> 00:04:59,320
我认为这是明智的举动
Well, I think it's a smart move.

71
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,530
既然不能否认  干嘛要隐瞒呢
You can't deny it, so why try to hide it?

72
00:05:01,530 --> 00:05:03,360
另外  我认为这也强调了
Plus, I think it underscores the importance

73
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,020
副总统选举的重要性
of the vice presidential situation.

74
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:07,810
等等  把捐赠者的妈妈拉出来  感觉像在作秀
Wait, rolling out the donor's mom? That feels a bit exploitative.

75
00:05:07,810 --> 00:05:09,160
我...等等
I... Look, hold on.

76
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:11,220
有点同情心  那孩子刚刚饮弹自尽了
A little bit of compassion, the kid just shot himself.

77
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:13,150
而且是用一把手枪
And with a handgun, no less.

78
00:05:13,150 --> 00:05:14,970
合法购买的  不要把重点转移到枪上
Legally purchased. Let's not put this on the gun.

79
00:05:14,970 --> 00:05:17,370
很抱歉  这一切
Look, I am sorry, all of this, the whole thing,

80
00:05:17,380 --> 00:05:19,090
党代会...都是制造戏剧效果
the convention... It's theatrics.

81
00:05:19,090 --> 00:05:20,340
闹起来吧
Hey, look, I... bring on the circus.

82
00:05:20,340 --> 00:05:22,820
比四天的专题广告片有趣多了
It's a lot more fun than some four-day infomercial.

83
00:05:22,820 --> 00:05:24,450
我们来说说竞选者吧
Let's talk about the contenders themselves.

84
00:05:24,460 --> 00:05:26,560
足有十多个
There's almost a dozen of 'em.

85
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:28,960
-你能小点声吗  -...确实有机会
- Can you, uh, lower that, please? - ...really have a chance.

86
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:30,410
杜兰特是头一个
Durant, first among 'em.

87
00:05:30,980 --> 00:05:32,320
这才第一天  上午11点
It's 11:00 in the morning, day one, 

88
00:05:32,330 --> 00:05:33,380
收视率比《艾伦秀》还高
and they're beating Ellen.

89
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:35,460
网站的流量也少了
Less traffic on the website, too.

90
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,760
看视频的人越来越少了
People aren't watching the videos as much.

91
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:39,510
这个卖了一百多万份
This sold over a million copies.

92
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,100
是网上阅读量的五倍
Five times that many read it online.

93
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:44,820
对  那是上个月  这是这个月
Yeah, well, that was last month. This is this month.

94
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:46,740
我们公开了一位重要竞选伙伴
We announce a stellar running mate.

95
00:05:47,470 --> 00:05:49,270
他在哈里发国问题上重创安德伍德
He eviscerates Underwood on ICO.

96
00:05:49,270 --> 00:05:51,130
我们手里有两个
We have not one, but two

97
00:05:51,130 --> 00:05:53,190
《名利场》封面供波利跳推送
Vanity Fair covers that Pollyhop's pushing,

98
00:05:53,190 --> 00:05:56,300
而你们却在这里大找借口
and all you give me is excuses.

99
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:58,660
应该是我们的曝光率压制他们的党代会
The point was for us to drown out their convention,

100
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:01,760
而不是反过来  我们得把风头夺回来
not the other way around. We need to steal the thunder back.

101
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,470
那就去风口夺风头
So go where the thunder is.

102
00:06:07,010 --> 00:06:10,370
两年来  我一直近在咫尺
I've been one heartbeat away for almost two years.

103
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,570
我对这个已经没兴趣了
My heart's not in it anymore.

104
00:06:13,070 --> 00:06:16,070
过了11月我就回佛蒙特去了
I'm going to head back to Vermont after November.

105
00:06:16,610 --> 00:06:18,140
也许继续回去教书
Maybe start teaching again.

106
00:06:19,070 --> 00:06:20,540
那你支持谁呢
Who are you supporting, then?

107
00:06:20,850 --> 00:06:22,500
公开说是凯茜·杜兰特
On the record, Cathy Durant.

108
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,210
私下里呢
And off the record?

109
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:28,920
我不是很喜欢她
I'm not the biggest fan.

110
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:30,220
为什么
Why?

111
00:06:30,980 --> 00:06:33,500
俄国危机期间她没帮上什么忙
She wasn't much help during the Russia crisis.

112
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:35,050
可是她和佩特罗夫达成了协议
She closed the deal with Petrov. 

113
00:06:35,050 --> 00:06:36,920
功劳的确是归到她头上了
She took credit for it, sure.

114
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:40,460
但她从始至终都在阻挠那份协议
But she fought the deal every step of the way.

115
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:43,630
如果不是克莱尔  根本就不可能成
Nothing would've happened if it weren't for Claire.

116
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:44,770
第一夫人
The First Lady?

117
00:06:46,130 --> 00:06:47,510
是前大使
The former ambassador.

118
00:06:48,610 --> 00:06:51,350
我们在堪萨斯支持率更接近了  但还不够
We're closer in Kansas, but still not close enough.

119
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:52,330
你去争取众议院票时
Did you speak to Jefferies

120
00:06:52,330 --> 00:06:54,240
和杰弗瑞斯谈过了吗
when you were there for the House vote?

121
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,870
他正在向弗雷德·西姆斯施压
He's leaning on Fred Simms.

122
00:06:55,870 --> 00:06:58,130
如果西姆斯可以拉来两三名代表
If Simms could deliver two or three delegates--

123
00:06:58,130 --> 00:06:59,630
那就能整个拿下堪萨斯了
That could push Kansas over the edge.

124
00:06:59,630 --> 00:07:00,640
我可以联系乌麦克
I can call Womack.

125
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:01,990
他在那边有几个朋友
He's got some friends over the border.

126
00:07:01,990 --> 00:07:03,590
-珀利怎么样  -珀利
- What about Pawley? - Pawley?

127
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:06,440
沃思堡治安官珀利  是我爸的老朋友了
Sheriff Pawley in Fort Worth, old family friend of my dad's.

128
00:07:06,450 --> 00:07:08,580
他和达拉斯的几位超级代表关系很近
He's close with some superdelegates from Dallas.

129
00:07:08,590 --> 00:07:09,760
可以拉他过来
Yes, he's on board.

130
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:10,750
真得喜欢这些治安官
Gotta love those sheriffs.

131
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:12,340
我们在路易斯安那就是那么做的
That's how we do in Louisiana. 

132
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:13,080
恩莱特呢
What about Enright?

133
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:14,590
我和他约好了在凯悦喝咖啡
I'm meeting him for coffee at the Hyatt.

134
00:07:14,590 --> 00:07:16,560
话说我该过去了  我可不想迟到
In fact, I better get going. I don't wanna be late.

135
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,540
如果我们能拿下弗吉尼亚
Now, if we could lock up Virginia--

136
00:07:18,540 --> 00:07:20,080
就会向全国发出强势的讯息
It would send a very big message.

137
00:07:20,090 --> 00:07:22,010
接下来就是肯塔基
And then Kentucky next.

138
00:07:22,010 --> 00:07:23,720
肯塔基州可喜欢你了
He's got a big old crush on you.

139
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:25,460
那你最好赶紧上路
We better get you on a move.

140
00:07:25,460 --> 00:07:28,110
恩莱特最讨厌不守时了
Enright is a stickler for punctuality.

141
00:07:28,110 --> 00:07:31,080
我挺开心的  我都忘了我多喜欢做党鞭
You know, I'm having fun. I forgot how much I miss being whip.

142
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:33,510
鞭子你来抽  蜜糖我来喂
You whip 'em. I'll sweet talk 'em.

143
00:07:33,510 --> 00:07:35,590
胡萝卜加大棒最有效了
Nothing like leather and sugar.

144
00:07:36,450 --> 00:07:37,400
先生
Sir?

145
00:07:38,490 --> 00:07:39,560
希尔参议员
Senator Sheer.

146
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:42,700
参议员  你干得太漂亮了
Senator, you did a fine job.

147
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:44,380
我最好能拿到黄金时段
Yeah, I better get prime time,

148
00:07:44,390 --> 00:07:46,140
而不是在垃圾时段发表讲话
not one of these midmorning speeches.

149
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:50,070
周三晚上八点  我亲自和帕特打招呼
Eight o'clock, Wednesday night. I called Patti myself.

150
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:51,790
你知道政客这个物种
Do you know the main thing that separates 

151
00:07:51,790 --> 00:07:54,690
和其他物种最大的区别是什么吗
a politician from the rest of the species?

152
00:07:54,690 --> 00:07:57,420
政客愿意淹死一窝小奶猫
A politician is the one who would drown a litter of kittens

153
00:07:57,420 --> 00:07:59,870
来换十分钟的黄金时段
for ten minutes of prime time.

154
00:08:00,790 --> 00:08:04,220
杜兰特国务卿  我是政治新闻网的总编
Secretary Durant. Editor in chief, Politico.

155
00:08:04,220 --> 00:08:05,150
没事的
It's all right.

156
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:07,810
亚当  你亲自来做报道吗
Adam, are you covering this yourself?

157
00:08:07,810 --> 00:08:09,430
68年以来的第一次开放党代会
First open one since '68.

158
00:08:09,430 --> 00:08:10,450
不过这天够潮的
It's humid as hell, though.

159
00:08:10,450 --> 00:08:12,280
我刚来就浑身透湿了
I just got here and I'm already soaked.

160
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:12,920
不过往好处想
On the plus side,

161
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:15,690
我听说这里的艳舞俱乐部全国顶尖
I hear they have the best strip clubs in the country.

162
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:17,390
我能问几个问题吗
Can I ask you a couple questions?

163
00:08:17,390 --> 00:08:19,760
-我有点急事  -就几个
- Well, I'm in a hurry. - Just a couple.

164
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:21,060
不能公开
Nothing on the record.

165
00:08:22,690 --> 00:08:24,030
和我说说那些
Tell me about the rumors

166
00:08:24,030 --> 00:08:26,840
你在勃兰登堡和佩特罗夫谈判的传闻吧
regarding the deal you struck with Petrov in Brandenburg.

167
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:28,060
什么传闻
What rumors?

168
00:08:28,060 --> 00:08:30,950
是第一夫人谈妥的协议  而不是你
That it was the First Lady who brokered the deal, not you.

