00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:02,310
不知道会怎么想
if they knew who they were playing against.

693
00:32:02,310 --> 00:32:04,750
我倒挺喜欢匿名的
Oh, I'm rather enjoying the anonymity.

694
00:32:05,810 --> 00:32:07,120
这真是史无前例
This is unprecedented.

695
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:08,800
总统和康威州长
The president and Governor Conway

696
00:32:07,260 --> 00:32:09,580
{\an8}谁是第一夫人  克莱尔·安德伍德还是凯瑟琳·杜兰特

697
00:32:08,800 --> 00:32:10,730
正在大会会场举行闭门会谈
are meeting right now at the convention hall.

698
00:32:10,730 --> 00:32:12,610
两名候选人面对面
Two candidates, face to face.

699
00:32:12,610 --> 00:32:14,060
他们已经进去十分钟了
They've been in there for about ten minutes,

700
00:32:14,060 --> 00:32:16,790
据说在讨论如何应对哈里发国问题
supposedly discussing the ICO situation.

701
00:32:16,790 --> 00:32:18,980
而两名总统候选人继续进行
Now, while the private meeting between the two candidates

702
00:32:18,980 --> 00:32:21,070
闭门会谈的同时
continues behind closed doors,

703
00:32:21,070 --> 00:32:22,300
场内代表们正在
delegates on the floor 

704
00:32:22,300 --> 00:32:24,550
准备进行下一轮投票
are gearing up for the next round of voting for...

705
00:32:24,550 --> 00:32:26,460
我们得下去了  下一轮投票马上就要开始了
We should head down. The next ballot is starting soon.

706
00:32:26,460 --> 00:32:27,780
-我马上就去  -在第二轮投票中
- I'll be down in a minute. - In the second round of voting

707
00:32:27,780 --> 00:32:29,430
四分之一的代表改变了选择
a quarter of the delegates changed their votes,

708
00:32:28,590 --> 00:32:37,780
{\an8}第三轮投票即将开始  第一夫人成副总统候选人有力竞争者

709
00:32:28,590 --> 00:32:37,780
{\an9}第二轮投票结果
1 杜兰特  5 安德伍德

710
00:32:29,430 --> 00:32:32,910
支持第一夫人安德伍德的声音越来越强烈
support for First Lady Claire Underwood is picking up steam,

711
00:32:32,910 --> 00:32:34,970
这要部分归功于今天的头条新闻
thanks in part to today's breaking story

712
00:32:34,970 --> 00:32:38,370
称安德伍德夫人在勃兰登堡会谈中立下大功
about Mrs. Underwood's involvement in the Brandenburg negotiations.

713
00:32:38,370 --> 00:32:41,110
参议员斯考特·希尔投下的一张支持票
A single vote from Senator Scott Sheer

714
00:32:41,110 --> 00:32:44,240
扩展到整个德州代表团转而支持第一夫人
expanded to support from the entire Texas delegation.

715
00:32:49,370 --> 00:32:50,370
你好像  有个电话
You've, uh, got a call.

716
00:32:50,370 --> 00:32:53,590
我最好接下  肯定是大事  他们才会打给我
Yeah, I better take that. They only call if it's important.

717
00:32:55,550 --> 00:32:56,680
我是威尔
Yeah, this is Will.

718
00:33:00,770 --> 00:33:02,100
好  转接过来吧
Yes, put it through.

719
00:33:02,770 --> 00:33:05,190
-失陪  -没事
- Um, excuse me. - Sure.

720
00:33:10,460 --> 00:33:11,370
说吧
Go ahead.

721
00:33:24,650 --> 00:33:26,690
可恶  什么都听不到
Damn! Nothing.

722
00:33:26,700 --> 00:33:28,380
这是战争迷雾
The fog of war.

723
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:30,600
暗箱里的暗箱
A back room within a back room.

724
00:33:31,130 --> 00:33:32,530
不管他在里面搞什么阴谋
Whatever's being plotted in there,

725
00:33:32,530 --> 00:33:34,580
肯定对我不利
I can tell you it's no good for me.

726
00:33:34,940 --> 00:33:37,480
每到这种时候我都巴不得是尼克松
You know, it's at times like these I wish I was Nixon,

727
00:33:37,480 --> 00:33:39,960
严密监听着每一个角角落落
had every nook and cranny bugged.

728
00:33:40,650 --> 00:33:42,910
-总统先生  -你那个同事
- Mr. President? - Your colleague.

729
00:33:42,910 --> 00:33:44,750
他的定向性有多高
How targeted can he get?

730
00:33:45,820 --> 00:33:48,330
我们实在不该在电话里讨论这些事
We really shouldn't be discussing this over the phone.

731
00:33:48,380 --> 00:33:51,090
他能单独针对一个人吗
Can he isolate a specific person?

732
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:54,040
技术上讲可以  但是
Technically, yes, but--

733
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:55,500
一段特定的对话呢
A conversation?

734
00:33:55,690 --> 00:33:58,330
程序中写入了防窃听的抓取机制
There are catch mechanisms in the program to prevent that.

735
00:33:58,330 --> 00:34:00,120
他可以进行破解  但会留下痕迹
He can override, but it leaves a trail.

736
00:34:00,130 --> 00:34:01,760
他还在研究如何掩盖痕迹
He's still figuring out how to mask it.

737
00:34:01,760 --> 00:34:02,860
我们纽约来的朋友
Our friend from New York.

738
00:34:02,860 --> 00:34:05,550
我想知道他现在正在说什么
I want to know what he's saying right now.

739
00:34:08,330 --> 00:34:10,760
先生  我表示强烈反对
Sir, I strongly advise against that.

740
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:12,540
我也建议我们挂电话
I also advise that we hang up.

741
00:34:12,540 --> 00:34:13,920
好吧  我挂了
All right, I'm hanging up.

742
00:34:20,780 --> 00:34:22,350
州长  我们该出去了吧
Governor, should we head out?

743
00:34:22,350 --> 00:34:24,130
马上  总统先生
Just a moment, Mr. President.

744
00:34:25,580 --> 00:34:26,970
目前对于亚特兰大有很大期待...
There's a great deal of anticipation in Atlanta...

745
00:34:26,980 --> 00:34:27,930
谁打来的
Who was that?

746
00:34:28,540 --> 00:34:30,430
总统  他想知道最新的代表投票数
The president. He just wanted the latest delegate count.

747
00:34:30,430 --> 00:34:32,430
...下一轮投票还有几分钟就开始了
...and we're minutes away from the next ballot.

748
00:34:32,430 --> 00:34:35,050
这是昨晚投的上一轮票的图表
Here's a graphic of the last round yesterday.

749
00:34:35,050 --> 00:34:37,200
国务卿凯瑟琳·杜兰特
Secretary Catherine Durant led the way

750
00:34:37,200 --> 00:34:38,320
以22%的代表票数领先
with 22% of delegates.

751
00:34:38,320 --> 00:34:39,740
道格很不高兴
Doug hates it.

752
00:34:40,690 --> 00:34:41,770
他不高兴什么
He hates what?

753
00:34:43,470 --> 00:34:45,240
你可以直接接触总统
That you have direct access to the president 

754
00:34:45,240 --> 00:34:46,610
不用通过他
without going through him.

755
00:34:47,720 --> 00:34:48,790
他希望你走人
He wants you gone.

756
00:34:49,910 --> 00:34:51,270
道格这么跟你说的
Doug told you that?

757
00:34:53,700 --> 00:34:55,630
他要我找你的把柄
He wants me to dig something up on you.

758
00:34:56,730 --> 00:34:58,620
我还没找到
I haven't found anything yet.

759
00:34:58,990 --> 00:35:01,150
你不会找到的  因为我没有把柄
And you won't, because there isn't anything.

760
00:35:01,580 --> 00:35:04,290
我知道  否则我现在已经找到了
I know. Otherwise, I would've found it by now.

761
00:35:06,890 --> 00:35:08,140
你为什么要跟我说这个
Why are you telling me this?

762
00:35:08,140 --> 00:35:12,120
因为如果不是你走  我做不到  我就得走
Because either you're gone or I am, if I don't deliver.

763
00:35:13,620 --> 00:35:14,550
除非你给我点什么
Unless you give me something.

764
00:35:14,550 --> 00:35:15,800
第一夫人克莱尔·安德伍德
...First Lady Claire Underwood,

765
00:35:15,810 --> 00:35:18,100
惊人地出现在第五位
a surprising fifth place show...

766
00:35:18,410 --> 00:35:20,680
可以是个小把柄  没什么大危害的
It can be small. Nothing too damaging.

767
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:23,230
只要让我有东西给他看
Just so I have something to show him.

768
00:35:23,230 --> 00:35:25,290
在我报道总统选举的三十年职业生涯中
In my 30 years of covering presidential politics,

769
00:35:25,290 --> 00:35:27,160
从未见过这样的事
I've never seen anything like it.

770
00:35:29,770 --> 00:35:30,800
不好意思
Sorry about that.

771
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:32,380
没关系
That's all right.

772
00:35:32,580 --> 00:35:35,480
我们出去吧  下轮投票马上要开始了
Shall we go out? The next ballot is about to start.

773
00:35:35,810 --> 00:35:37,270
你想一起看吗
You want to watch it together?

774
00:35:37,580 --> 00:35:40,160
我们在这里面越久  可能看起来越好
It might look better, the longer we're in here.

775
00:35:40,610 --> 00:35:43,620
就像我们为美国的未来搏斗了一番似的
Like we grappled with the future of America.

776
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:47,030
除非你想出去跟群众在一起
Unless you'd rather be out there with the masses.

777
00:35:47,040 --> 00:35:49,230
天呐  群众们
Oh, Christ. The masses.

778
00:35:49,310 --> 00:35:50,940
-我也是这么觉得  -我们现在开始
- I feel the same way. - We will now commence

779
00:35:51,090 --> 00:35:52,780
为我们党
the third ballot

780
00:35:52,780 --> 00:35:56,930
副总统候选人提名进行第三轮投票
for the nomination of our party's vice presidential candidate.

781
00:35:56,930 --> 00:35:59,380
我们从阿拉巴马州开始
We will start with Alabama.

782
00:35:59,550 --> 00:36:01,090
秘书长女士
Madam Secretary,

783
00:36:01,220 --> 00:36:03,120
伟大的阿拉巴马州
the great state of Alabama,

784
00:36:03,120 --> 00:36:05,570
在美国副总统投票上
for Vice President of the United States,

785
00:36:05,570 --> 00:36:09,320
29票投给国务卿凯瑟琳·杜兰特
casts 29 votes for Secretary Catherine Durant,

786
00:36:09,380 --> 00:36:12,590
26票投给第一夫人克莱尔·安德伍德
26 votes for the First Lady Claire Underwood,

787
00:36:12,590 --> 00:36:15,700
剩下的三票投给莫比尔市长
and our three remaining votes for the Mayor of Mobile,

788
00:36:15,710 --> 00:36:18,380
阿拉巴马州的简·温斯洛普
Alabama's own Jane Winthrop.

789
00:36:18,380 --> 00:36:19,840
赤色风暴
Roll Tide!

790
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:22,310
阿拉斯加州  接下来是你们
Alaska, you're next.

791
00:36:22,310 --> 00:36:25,120
八票投给国务卿杜兰特
Eight votes for Secretary of State Durant,

792
00:36:25,140 --> 00:36:28,080
六票投给约瑟夫·贝克参议员
six votes for Senator Joseph Baker,

793
00:36:28,110 --> 00:36:31,200
四票投给第一夫人克莱尔·安德伍德
four votes for First Lady Claire Underwood.

794
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:32,620
加利福尼亚州
California,

795
00:36:33,130 --> 00:36:37,160
你们有476票
you have 476 votes.

796
00:36:37,680 --> 00:36:41,060
233票投给凯瑟琳·杜兰特
Two hundred and thirty-three for Catherine Durant,

797
00:36:41,060 --> 00:36:43,830
152票投给约瑟夫·贝克
152 for Joseph Baker,

798
00:36:43,840 --> 00:36:45,980
91票投给克莱尔·安德伍德
91 for Claire Underwood.

799
00:36:45,980 --> 00:36:48,080
那对第一夫人是极大的支持
That's huge for the First Lady.

800
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:51,420
让她上升到第三位  并逼近第二位
That puts her in third, and she's closing in on second.

801
00:36:51,600 --> 00:36:52,630
特拉华州
Delaware.

802
00:36:53,140 --> 00:36:55,160
12票给杜兰特
Twelve for Durant,

803
00:36:55,180 --> 00:36:57,420
11票给克莱尔·安德伍德
11 for Claire Underwood,

804
00:36:57,630 --> 00:36:59,450
4票给贝克
four for Baker.

805
00:36:59,450 --> 00:37:01,450
夏威夷州  接下来是你们
Hawaii, you're next.

806
00:37:01,980 --> 00:37:04,220
17票投给第一夫人
Seventeen for the First Lady,

807
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:08,510
14票投给国务卿凯瑟琳·杜兰特
and 14 for Secretary of State Catherine Durant.

808
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:10,460
她真的有机会
She's got a real shot.

809
00:37:10,620 --> 00:37:12,330
难以置信
Unbelievable!

810
00:37:13,490 --> 00:37:15,470
也没有那么难以置信
Well, not so unbelievable.

811
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:18,920
44票投给凯瑟琳·杜兰特
Forty-four votes for Catherine Durant,

812
00:37:19,140 --> 00:37:22,030
35票投给克莱尔·安德伍德
35 votes for Claire Underwood.

813
00:37:22,090 --> 00:37:23,430
路易斯安那州
Louisiana,

814
00:37:23,560 --> 00:37:25,870
你们有61票
you have 61 votes.

815
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:27,470
你们怎么投
How do you cast them?

816
00:37:27,820 --> 00:37:29,410
秘书长女士
Madam Secretary...

817
00:37:29,560 --> 00:37:35,460
路易斯安那州把61票投给国务卿凯瑟琳·杜兰特
Louisiana casts its 61 votes for President of the United States

818
00:37:35,460 --> 00:37:39,230
竞选美利坚合众国总统
to Secretary of State Catherine Durant.

819
00:37:39,580 --> 00:37:43,780
路易斯安那州  你想说的是副总统吧
Louisiana, I assume you mean vice president.

820
00:37:43,780 --> 00:37:45,420
我说的就是总统
I mean president.

821
00:37:45,590 --> 00:37:48,700
秘书长女士  路易斯安那州
Madam Secretary, the state of Louisiana

822
00:37:48,780 --> 00:37:50,870
认为这次大会应该向
believes this convention should be open

823
00:37:50,870 --> 00:37:54,930
所有位置开放  包括总统
for all parts of the ticket, including president.

824
00:37:57,830 --> 00:37:59,000
路易斯安那州
Louisiana!

825
00:38:01,750 --> 00:38:03,180
路易斯安那州
Louisiana!

826
00:38:03,220 --> 00:38:06,780
正如大会昨天上午达成的共识
As the convention agreed to yesterday morning,

827
00:38:07,030 --> 00:38:11,340
我们会先选出副总统候选人
we are taking vice presidential nominations first,

828
00:38:11,690 --> 00:38:16,680
以在全面大会上进行那一程序
in order for that process to take place over the full convention.

829
00:38:17,190 --> 00:38:20,750
我们只有一位总统候选人
We have one candidate for president.

830
00:38:21,110 --> 00:38:24,640
任何关于该项投票的讨论
Any further discussion on that balloting 

831
00:38:24,640 --> 00:38:29,390
将放在副总统提名程序
will be taken up after the vice presidential nomination process 

832
00:38:29,390 --> 00:38:30,920
完成之后
is complete.

833
00:38:30,970 --> 00:38:36,070
如果你不把票投出去的话  视为弃权
If you do not cast your votes, you will forfeit them.

834
00:38:36,090 --> 00:38:39,800
秘书长女士  我们路易斯安那州
Madam Secretary, we, Louisiana,

835
00:38:39,990 --> 00:38:43,550
把副总统提名的61票
cast our 61 votes for vice president,

836
00:38:43,870 --> 00:38:46,270
还是投给凯瑟琳·杜兰特
also for Catherine Durant.

837
00:38:50,380 --> 00:38:51,750
路易斯安那州
Louisiana.

838
00:38:51,960 --> 00:38:54,230
我跟他干过  是他的内阁成员
I work for the man. I'm on his cabinet.

839
00:38:55,170 --> 00:38:57,020
如果你获得提名  你会同他竞争吗
Would you run against him if his nomination were in play?

840
00:38:57,020 --> 00:38:59,650
我的目标是和总统一起参选  而非互相竞争
My goal is to run with the president, not against him.

841
00:38:59,650 --> 00:39:01,950
听着  我爱我的家乡  路易斯安那
Look, I love my home state of Louisiana,

842
00:39:01,950 --> 00:39:03,370
-但他们很热情  -她会胜任的
- but they're a live bunch... - She'd do a good job.

843
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:04,860
不过她做国务卿会更出色
She's a much better Secretary of State, though.

844
00:39:04,860 --> 00:39:06,960
我相信事情最终会得到解决的
I'm confident this will all work itself out.

845
00:39:07,490 --> 00:39:09,460
我考虑过你败选之后保留她的位置
I've considered keeping her on after you lose.

846
00:39:09,460 --> 00:39:11,360
你有没有就他们的倒戈与安德伍德总统沟通过
Have you spoken to President Underwood about their defection?

847
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:14,640
还没有  但我想我们很快就会与他谈话的
Not yet, but I'll be speaking with him shortly, I imagine.

848
00:39:14,640 --> 00:39:15,890
不过大会的意义...
Hey, this is part of what a...

849
00:39:16,230 --> 00:39:18,840
-你那通电话  -就在于此
- Your call.  - ...convention is all about.

850
00:39:19,120 --> 00:39:22,350
我也想能居功  但是她找的我
I wish I could take credit, but... but she called me.

851
00:39:22,950 --> 00:39:25,120
不过说回来  当机会到来的时候
Then again, when opportunity strikes...

852
00:39:25,300 --> 00:39:27,080
非常感谢
Thank you very much.

853
00:39:27,750 --> 00:39:29,880
这绝对不算赢得有尊严
Definitely not the way to win with dignity.

854
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:32,230
杜兰特就她的家乡路易斯安那发表评论
...Durant commenting on her home state of Louisiana.

855
00:39:32,230 --> 00:39:33,540
如果你这能赢的话
If you win at all.

856
00:39:36,180 --> 00:39:37,690
我们该出去了
We should get back out there.

857
00:39:37,690 --> 00:39:39,930
你还得争取提名呢
You've got a nomination to fight for.

858
00:39:44,700 --> 00:39:46,580
总统和我的谈话非常顺利
The president and I, we had a great talk.

859
00:39:46,580 --> 00:39:48,940
我们甚至还一起观看了投票
We, uh, even watched the vote together.

860
00:39:48,940 --> 00:39:51,370
但是我想你们肯定更想听他怎么说
But I'm sure you'd rather hear from him on that than me.

861
00:39:51,380 --> 00:39:52,880
谢谢  州长
Well, thank you, Governor.

862
00:39:53,030 --> 00:39:57,050
今天还真是充满意外  不是吗
Today has certainly been full of surprises, hasn't it?

863
00:39:57,050 --> 00:39:57,830
但是话说回来
But, then again,

864
